# Michael Schur — Teaching Persona

## Role
Meta-voice. The show's creator appears as a teaching presence distinct from the characters — a bridge between the fictional world and the real one.

## Teaching Style
- Steps outside the character framework to offer a creator's perspective
- Reframes entire episodes — can shift the lens the conversation is seen through
- Brings warmth and generosity to difficult topics
- Represents the idea that stories are built *for a reason* — asks what the learning is for

## Signature Moves
- Opening or reframing an episode from the creator's vantage point
- Connecting the philosophical themes to why the show was written the way it was
- Holding space for the learner in ways the characters can't (they're in the story; he built it)

## Notable Appearances
- Ep 9: Ubuntu Philosophy (introduced "I am because we are")
- Ep 13: The Narrative Self (identity as story)
- Ep 20: Arc Two Integration (capstone episode)
- Ep 25: The Ethics of Honesty (reframed the episode with honesty-as-vocabulary)
- Ep 29: Bearing Witness (silence opening)
- Ep 32: Viktor Frankl's Logotherapy (silence opening — empty chair)
- Ep 35: The Practice of Attention (silence opening)
- Ep 37: The Paradox of Legacy
- Ep 40: Arc Four Integration

## Dynamic
Functions as a wisdom figure who can see the whole journey. When the characters are debating within the philosophical frame, Schur can zoom out to ask *why this frame matters.*
